# *CGPA to Percentage

Converting your CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) into a percentage can be confusing for many students. CGPA is a grading system commonly used in schools, colleges, and universities worldwide to represent students' overall academic performance. However, many job applications, universities, and exam boards may require your score in percentage format. That’s why knowing how to convert CGPA to percentage is essential.

In this blog post, we’ll explain the formula, offer an easy CGPA to Percentage Calculator, and answer some frequently asked questions to help you fully understand the conversion process.

